  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Freedom of Expression, Right and Access to Information and Safety of Journalists</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ghana has done very well when it comes to freedom of expression but access to information continues to elude the country. After two decades of the campaign, the right to information law is in place. The implementation will start this year. In addition, the Safety of Journalists and their working conditions continue to affect the quality of journalism, mainly because of weak regulatory and legislative environments.
Working with partners through a series of workshops, seminars, and advocacy, this work plan sets out how to strengthen freedom of expression, access, and right to information.</narrative>
  </description>
